# =============================================================================
# ESA Backend - Environment Configuration Example
# =============================================================================
#
# This application uses a unified configuration system:
#
# 1. YAML Config Files (backend/config/*.yaml)
#    - app.yaml      : Flask settings, logging, session
#    - database.yaml : Database connections
#    - apis.yaml     : External API settings (SOAP, SugarCRM)
#    - oauth.yaml    : Microsoft OAuth settings
#    - scheduler.yaml: Scheduler settings, alerts
#
# 2. Encrypted Vault (backend/python/.vault/)
#    - All passwords, API keys, secrets stored encrypted
#    - Managed via Admin UI at /admin/secrets
#
# 3. Root .env File (../.env)
#    - Contains ONLY the VAULT_MASTER_KEY
#    - This is the bootstrap secret that unlocks the vault
#
# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy the root .env.example to ../.env:
#    cp ../.env.example ../.env
#
# 2. Generate a vault master key:
#    python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
#
# 3. Set VAULT_MASTER_KEY in ../.env
#
# 4. Run the vault setup script:
#    python scripts/setup_vault.py
#
# 5. Add secrets via Admin UI or CLI:
#    python -c "from common.config_loader import get_config; c=get_config(); c.set_secret('DB_PASSWORD', 'xxx')"
#
# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED SECRETS (add to vault):
# =============================================================================
# DB_PASSWORD          - Backend database password
# PBI_DB_PASSWORD      - PBI database password
# FLASK_SECRET_KEY     - Flask session secret
# JWT_SECRET           - JWT signing key
# MS_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET - Microsoft OAuth secret
# SOAP_API_KEY         - SMD SOAP API key
# SOAP_CORP_PASSWORD   - SMD SOAP password
# SUGARCRM_PASSWORD    - SugarCRM password
# VM_SSH_PASSWORD      - Azure VM SSH password
# SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL    - Slack alerts webhook (optional)
# =============================================================================
